<CaseStudyLayout
  title="StreamSets Cloud"
  tagline="A top-down redesign of the StreamSets Platform experience."
  role="Design Lead"
  year="2018–2019"
  slug="sscloud"
>
  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/main.gif" alt="StreamSets Cloud platform overview" />
  </figure>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    StreamSets Cloud was a complete reimagining of the StreamSets platform — a tool for
    designing, running, and monitoring data pipelines at scale. The existing product had
    grown organically over several years, and the jump from on-prem to cloud gave us a
    chance to rethink core flows from the ground up: onboarding, pipeline design,
    monitoring, and team collaboration.
  </p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <p>
    Four major feature areas drove the redesign: a new pipeline canvas, rich telemetry
    and monitoring, collaborative workspaces, and an onboarding experience that could
    guide first-time users without getting in the way of experienced ones.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/group20.png" alt="StreamSets Cloud — pipeline canvas" />
  </figure>
  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/group21.png" alt="StreamSets Cloud — monitoring" />
  </figure>
  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/group22.png" alt="StreamSets Cloud — workspaces" />
  </figure>
  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/group24.png" alt="StreamSets Cloud — feature area" />
  </figure>

  <h2>Process &amp; Iteration</h2>
  <p>
    Every major flow went through rapid iteration cycles — whiteboard sketches, mid-fi
    Figma prototypes, and usability sessions with internal engineers and pilot customers.
    The pipeline canvas went through five distinct iterations before we locked on a
    direction that balanced screen real estate with the density of information
    experienced users wanted to see.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/group25.png" alt="Design iteration artifacts" />
  </figure>

  <h2>First-Time User Walkthrough</h2>
  <p>
    One of the hardest problems was onboarding. New users landed in an empty workspace
    and had no idea what to do first. We built a lightweight, contextual walkthrough
    that introduced the concept of pipelines with a working example — so the first
    thing you saw was data actually flowing.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/sscloud/walkthrough.gif" alt="First-time user walkthrough" />
  </figure>
</CaseStudyLayout>
